channel.title: Please help me!
channel.description: My computer (Toshiba laptop with vista) isnt connecting to the internet even though it had before. When i try to connect to my internet it connects but it says exactly this: "Currently connected to: Unidentifid network(2WIRE389)" and under that it says "Access: Local Only" when run my mouse over the internet button on the bottom toolbar. But then i try to open up Internet Explorer, Safari, Or Firefox and NONE of them work. It says i am connected to the Network but not the internet. I have tried hooking the ethernet cable up to my laptop and it still doesnt work. It is not my motem because im on my moms laptop right now wirelessly and it runs fine. Any tips how to fix it???

item.title: Please help me!
item.dc:creator: @NewbieNewty Newty
item.description:
@NewbieNewty wrote:

It’s a problem with Vista (or so it seems) because I have the same issue. Whenever you plug your computer into a new network it has issuses for some reason. So simply unplug your modem and plug it back in. If that doesn’t resolve it, or you don’t have access to your modem, then open up your network connections, right click whichever type of connection you are using (Local Area connection or Wireless) and click properties. Then click TCP/IPv4 and select properties. Then click obtain IP address automaticly. Click OK, give it some time and it should work now. You might need to do the same with TCP/IPv6. Hope that works for you, it did for me.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: June 24, 2009, 02:21:56 pm[/size][hr][quote=“the hunt”]how the fuck are you posting here then…[/quote]
